					<msContents>
						<summary>King Kulottuṅga Cōḻa gives endowment to a high-status <foreign>pāṇaṉ</foreign> for appointment of <foreign>pāṇars</foreign> to sing to Lord of Tiruviṭaimarutūr–for which he received <foreign>kāṇi</foreign>–and to train temple dancers (<foreign>taḷiyillār</foreign> and <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign>), for which he received gold, paddy and a house.
							<!--							There is a partial translation in Archeology of Bhakti. Hagiography vs History p. 331-332-->
							</summary>
